  "prompt": "How do I know if someone blocks me on Facebook messenger?",
  "response": "Here are some signs that someone may have blocked you on Facebook Messenger:\n\n1. Message status\n- Your messages will show as \"Sent\" but not \"Delivered\"\n- You won't see the person's \"Active\" or online status\n\n2. Profile and contact information\n- You can't see their profile picture\n- Their name may appear grayed out\n- You can't find their profile when searching\n\n3. Call and video chat features\n- You can't start a video or voice call with them\n- Existing call/chat options are unavailable\n\n4. Check conversation history\n- Previous conversations might still be visible\n- You can't send new messages that will reach them\n\n5. Confirming the block\n- Ask a mutual friend if they can see the person's profile\n- Create a new Facebook account to check if you can find their profile\n\nKeep in mind that these signs could also indicate that the person:\n- Deactivated their account\n- Changed privacy settings\n- Has poor internet connection\n- Unfriended you (slightly different from blocking)\n\nThe most definitive way to confirm is through direct communication with the person.",
